DOT-VIM: My ~/.vim directory containing plugins and customizations for the vim editor (version 7.0 and up).

For full support, configure and compile vim with ruby support.

Installation: (*nix)
  cd 
  git clone <url>
  mv dot-vim .vim
  ln -s .vim/vimrc .vimrc

Included parts
  rails.vim
  matchit
  NERD_Tree    (:NERDTree to start)
  fuzzyfinder
  fuzzyfinder_textmate (Configured to ^T, needs ruby support compiled into vim)
  misc. themes
  completion   (F1 configured to complete, you can change to TAB or other)
  sample .vimrc files from around the internets

  Many thanks to those who contributed the above modules and the vim community!
